title: [Whistler's Pass, Rocky Field]
description: The trail becomes exceedingly rocky as it continues down the mountainside.  Pebbles cover the trail, interspersed with larger stones, hidden in the dark of night.  A halfling-sized boulder rests near the trail, seemingly the perfect place to stop and rest sore feet.
